import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lat'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Latitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_5 = data['key'].value_counts().nlargest(5)
    plt.bar(top_5.index, top_5.values)
    plt.title("What are the top 5 most common categories in the 'key' field?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    std = data['lat'].std()
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(x=std, color='red', label=f'Standard Deviation: {std:.2f}')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the standard deviation of the \'lat\' field?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(data['lat'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['lat'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].min(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Min: {data['lat'].min():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['lat'].max(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Max: {data['lat'].max():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the minimum and maximum value of the 'lat' field?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    colors = {'bubbletea': 'red', 'korean': 'green', 'coffee': 'blue'}
    for key in colors.keys():
        x = data[data['key'] == key]['lat']
        y = data[data['key'] == key].index
        ax.scatter(x, y, c=colors[key], label=key, alpha=0.5)
    ax.legend()
    plt.title("What is the correlation between the 'key' and 'lat' fields?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
